I'm using a Fragment (not Compose) and I want to collect a Flow from my ViewModel and update the UI. My current code sometimes crashes or shows stale data after the fragment comes back from the back stack. What is the correct pattern, and why does my current approach have a problem?

```kotlin
class OrdersFragment : Fragment(R.layout.fragment_orders) {
    private val viewModel: OrdersViewModel by viewModels()

    override fun onViewCreated(view: View, savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
        super.onViewCreated(view, savedInstanceState)
        lifecycleScope.launch {
            viewModel.orders.collect { orders ->
                adapter.submitList(orders)
            }
        }
    }
}
